1
00:00:09,062 --> 00:00:09,858
<i>C'mon!</i>

2
00:00:16,202 --> 00:00:18,830
<i>Running like a fugitive,</i>

3
00:00:19,872 --> 00:00:22,033
<i>Being chased by something</i>

4
00:00:23,710 --> 00:00:26,372
<i>Inside my heart is pounding</i>

5
00:00:27,480 --> 00:00:30,108
<i>My throat dry like it's withering</i>

6
00:00:31,818 --> 00:00:34,912
<i>For no single one,</i>

7
00:00:35,422 --> 00:00:38,687
<i>To none does belong,</i>

8
00:00:40,160 --> 00:00:44,426
<i>This time is ours, right now...</i>

9
00:00:47,067 --> 00:00:48,932
<i>Unraveling the pain,</i>

10
00:00:49,035 --> 00:00:50,764
<i>Unraveling our hearts,</i>

11
00:00:50,837 --> 00:00:53,169
<i>Unraveling shadows</i>

12
00:00:54,708 --> 00:00:56,471
<i>Stifling our breath,</i>

13
00:00:56,543 --> 00:00:58,443
<i>Reaching for beyond,</i>

14
00:00:58,511 --> 00:01:00,945
<i>Tearing through the dark</i>

15
00:01:02,849 --> 00:01:09,413
<i>In fighting and in love</i>

16
00:01:10,390 --> 00:01:13,018
<i>To the distant light above,</i>

17
00:01:13,460 --> 00:01:16,657
<i>Yes, we are on the way</i>

18
00:01:21,401 --> 00:01:22,698
<i>I wanna rock...</i>

19
00:01:25,271 --> 00:01:26,795
<i>Rockin' my heart</i>

20
00:01:51,792 --> 00:01:53,623
It looks like you've got some time
to kill there all by yourself.

21
00:01:55,863 --> 00:01:58,832
What happened to the blond boy
and that stuck up boy?

22
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:00,992
They're in the middle of
the tree-climbing training.

23
00:02:01,502 --> 00:02:02,730
You don't have to do that?

24
00:02:03,370 --> 00:02:07,397
I'm exceptional, so Kakashi Sensei
told me to guard you.

25
00:02:09,810 --> 00:02:10,504
Really?

26
00:02:11,612 --> 00:02:12,943
What?!

27
00:02:15,015 --> 00:02:16,539
You got a minute, Tazuna?

28
00:02:17,751 --> 00:02:19,309
Huh? What's up, Giichi?

29
00:02:20,020 --> 00:02:21,578
Uh, actually...

30
00:02:22,189 --> 00:02:24,123
I gave it a lot of thought.

31
00:02:24,592 --> 00:02:28,187
Building this bridge...
will you let me quit?

32
00:02:28,662 --> 00:02:32,428
Why so suddenly? Not you too?!

33
00:02:33,467 --> 00:02:36,527
Tazuna, I've had a bond
with you from the old days.

34
00:02:37,037 --> 00:02:39,301
I'd like to cooperate,
but if we push it too far,

35
00:02:39,373 --> 00:02:41,773
Gato will set his sights
on us, too.

36
00:02:44,178 --> 00:02:48,114
Also... if you get killed,
everything is lost!

37
00:02:50,351 --> 00:02:54,048
Why don't you just
stop building the bridge?

38
00:02:59,026 --> 00:03:00,516
Not a chance...

39
00:03:02,463 --> 00:03:04,488
This is our bridge.

40
00:03:05,199 --> 00:03:08,168
This is the bridge that
everyone in town has built

41
00:03:08,302 --> 00:03:11,396
believing that it would generate
distribution and transportation

42
00:03:11,472 --> 00:03:13,736
for this poor Land of Waves
that has few resources.

43
00:03:14,441 --> 00:03:16,807
But if it goes so far as
to take our lives...

44
00:03:17,711 --> 00:03:19,008
It's already afternoon...

45
00:03:19,446 --> 00:03:20,913
Let's call it a day.

46
00:03:23,083 --> 00:03:23,742
Tazuna!

47
00:03:25,819 --> 00:03:28,686
Giichi... you don't have to
come back tomorrow.

48
00:03:34,595 --> 00:03:40,465
<i>The Land Where a Hero Once Lived</i>

49
00:03:41,936 --> 00:03:43,836
Damn it!

50
00:03:46,440 --> 00:03:48,408
What the heck is up with this?

51
00:04:05,292 --> 00:04:07,226
<i>I won't lose to you!</i>

52
00:04:23,577 --> 00:04:25,408
Say, where are we going?

53
00:04:25,679 --> 00:04:29,080
I was asked to get some ingredients
for dinner on the way home...

54
00:04:29,216 --> 00:04:31,616
WILL DO ANY KIND OF WORK

55
00:04:32,019 --> 00:04:32,951
Thief!

56
00:04:40,294 --> 00:04:41,852
<i>What's up with... this town?</i>

57
00:04:43,364 --> 00:04:44,388
We're here...

58
00:04:45,466 --> 00:04:46,433
Welcome...

59
00:04:57,411 --> 00:04:59,038
<i>There's hardly anything here...</i>

60
00:05:05,719 --> 00:05:08,051
You pervert!!

61
00:05:09,023 --> 00:05:11,184
You're... wrong...

62
00:05:14,962 --> 00:05:17,624
Man, I was really surprised earlier.

63
00:05:18,065 --> 00:05:19,794
What's going on with this town?!

64
00:05:21,969 --> 00:05:22,594
<i>Again?</i>

65
00:05:23,771 --> 00:05:24,362
Hey, you...

66
00:05:28,442 --> 00:05:28,931
What?

67
00:05:30,477 --> 00:05:31,409
Gimme some!

68
00:05:42,756 --> 00:05:44,917
Oh... Here...

69
00:05:46,126 --> 00:05:47,024
Yaaay!

70
00:05:48,796 --> 00:05:49,820
Thank you.

71
00:05:55,436 --> 00:05:57,370
This is how it's been ever
since Gato showed up.

72
00:05:58,172 --> 00:06:01,471
Here, all the adults
have turned into cowards.

73
00:06:07,548 --> 00:06:11,143
So that's why now
that bridge is necessary...

74
00:06:12,086 --> 00:06:13,519
It's a symbol of bravery...

75
00:06:14,154 --> 00:06:17,214
in order to restore their spirit,
so they don't keep running away...

76
00:06:17,291 --> 00:06:18,781
For the people of this land...

77
00:06:18,859 --> 00:06:20,793
who have set their minds
on remaining passive...

78
00:06:23,831 --> 00:06:28,564
If we can just...
complete that bridge...

79
00:06:30,871 --> 00:06:33,362
this town will return to
how it once was...

80
00:06:34,575 --> 00:06:36,440
and everyone will come back.

81
00:06:45,886 --> 00:06:47,945
<i>Sasuke... Naruto...</i>

82
00:07:05,572 --> 00:07:06,800
<i>Damn it! Damn it!</i>

83
00:07:07,141 --> 00:07:09,507
<i>Are you telling me that</i>
<i>Sasuke's still climbing?!</i>

84
00:07:14,381 --> 00:07:14,972
<i>Darn it...</i>

85
00:07:15,282 --> 00:07:16,909
<i>He's gradually catching up...</i>

86
00:07:19,486 --> 00:07:22,683
<i>Darn it! No! No!</i>

87
00:07:23,357 --> 00:07:27,293
<i>If I let myself get distracted by Sasuke,</i>
<i>my concentration will be disturbed!</i>

88
00:07:29,530 --> 00:07:33,193
Hey Sakura,
can you give me some tips?

89
00:07:33,734 --> 00:07:34,132
Huh?

90
00:07:34,935 --> 00:07:37,096
Without telling Sasuke, okay, okay?

91
00:07:38,872 --> 00:07:39,566
Listen.

92
00:07:39,706 --> 00:07:44,905
Chakra uses spiritual energy,
so you mustn't get too strained or frantic.

93
00:07:45,412 --> 00:07:48,575
Relax and concentrate on the tree
so that you can constantly accumulate

94
00:07:48,649 --> 00:07:50,879
a fixed amount of Chakra
in the bottom of your feet.

95
00:07:51,785 --> 00:07:53,446
<i>Concentrate!</i>
<i>Concentrate!</i>

96
00:07:53,754 --> 00:07:56,279
<i>Okay. I'm getting good vibes, I say!</i>

97
00:07:56,890 --> 00:07:58,357
<i>Okay! This is it!</i>

98
00:07:58,525 --> 00:07:59,287
Hey... Naruto!

99
00:08:01,862 --> 00:08:04,524
Jeez, what the heck's
wrong with you?!

100
00:08:04,831 --> 00:08:06,765
Don't interfere while
I'm trying to concentrate!

101
00:08:07,534 --> 00:08:10,332
U... Uh... Well...

102
00:08:11,305 --> 00:08:12,829
W-What is it?!

103
00:08:14,474 --> 00:08:17,443
<i>I'm not used to</i>
<i>him speaking to me first...</i>

104
00:08:20,380 --> 00:08:24,339
Y-You asked Sakura to give
you some tips before...

105
00:08:25,018 --> 00:08:26,679
What did she say to you?

106
00:08:31,358 --> 00:08:32,723
I'm not telling!

107
00:08:48,709 --> 00:08:49,641
Man...

108
00:08:49,710 --> 00:08:51,234
This is really fun!

109
00:08:51,311 --> 00:08:54,542
It's been a long time since we've had
a meal with this many people!

110
00:09:01,255 --> 00:09:02,119
Seconds please!

111
00:09:08,128 --> 00:09:10,289
Stop eating if you're going to vomit!

112
00:09:10,797 --> 00:09:12,264
No, I'll eat.

113
00:09:13,133 --> 00:09:15,033
I have to eat even
if it means enduring.

114
00:09:15,435 --> 00:09:17,926
I have to get strong
as quickly as possible, so...

115
00:09:18,739 --> 00:09:19,706
Yes yes!

116
00:09:20,374 --> 00:09:22,706
But vomiting is different.

117
00:09:29,283 --> 00:09:33,219
Excuse me, why is there
a torn picture hanging here?

118
00:09:34,154 --> 00:09:37,021
Inari was looking at this
all through dinner.

119
00:09:37,190 --> 00:09:42,287
This torn part looks like someone who was
in the picture was deliberately torn off.

120
00:09:47,567 --> 00:09:48,499
It's my husband...

121
00:09:50,771 --> 00:09:53,763
He's a man who was
once called a hero of this town...

122
00:09:57,511 --> 00:09:59,103
Inari! Where are you going?

123
00:10:06,520 --> 00:10:07,282
Dad!

124
00:10:07,587 --> 00:10:10,454
I'm always telling you not to
talk about that person in front of Inari!

125
00:10:21,835 --> 00:10:24,463
What're you saying happened with Inari?

126
00:10:25,505 --> 00:10:28,269
It appears there's
some kind of good reason.

127
00:10:30,010 --> 00:10:33,377
Inari had a father
not related by blood...

128
00:10:34,214 --> 00:10:37,877
It was like they were a real father
and son who got along really well...

129
00:10:40,687 --> 00:10:44,316
Back then, Inari was a child
who laughed all the time...

130
00:10:46,426 --> 00:10:47,222
However...

131
00:10:54,101 --> 00:10:55,125
However...

132
00:10:56,603 --> 00:11:02,303
Inari has changed...
ever since that incident with his father.

133
00:11:07,015 --> 00:11:09,506
The word bravery was eternally taken

134
00:11:09,584 --> 00:11:13,953
from the people of this island
and from Inari...

135
00:11:14,456 --> 00:11:17,289
With that day,
that incident, as the trigger.

136
00:11:18,426 --> 00:11:21,395
That incident?
What happened to Inari?

137
00:11:22,764 --> 00:11:25,631
To explain the incident,
I must first...

138
00:11:26,401 --> 00:11:30,804
tell you about the man
who was called the hero of this land.

139
00:11:31,372 --> 00:11:32,304
Hero?

140
00:11:33,241 --> 00:11:35,175
It was around three years ago...

141
00:11:35,844 --> 00:11:38,312
when Inari met the man...

142
00:11:41,216 --> 00:11:42,012
Potchi!!

143
00:11:42,183 --> 00:11:43,013
Potchi!!

144
00:11:45,653 --> 00:11:46,415
Wrong!

145
00:11:46,855 --> 00:11:48,982
His name's Shooting Star...

146
00:11:49,424 --> 00:11:50,982
As of today, he's my dog!

147
00:11:51,259 --> 00:11:54,558
He's not Shooting Star!
He's my Potchi! Give him back!

148
00:11:54,996 --> 00:11:56,520
Potchi's my friend!

149
00:11:56,798 --> 00:11:58,993
Who's going to give him
to the likes of you?!

150
00:12:01,002 --> 00:12:01,900
Shut up!

151
00:12:08,810 --> 00:12:09,504
Potchi!!

152
00:12:13,414 --> 00:12:15,712
That's cuz you wouldn't
hand him over quietly...

153
00:12:16,217 --> 00:12:18,276
Now I couldn't care less
about that dog!

154
00:12:19,220 --> 00:12:20,619
Hey, let him go!

155
00:12:22,257 --> 00:12:25,420
What have you done?!
Are you trying to kill Potchi?!

156
00:12:26,060 --> 00:12:29,029
Heh! He's your special mutt, right?

157
00:12:29,330 --> 00:12:31,093
Then save him, quick.

158
00:12:33,301 --> 00:12:34,734
What's the matter?

159
00:12:35,370 --> 00:12:36,962
Is it okay with you if he dies?!

160
00:12:44,245 --> 00:12:45,906
<i>Of course I'm not okay</i>
<i>with him dying!</i>

161
00:12:46,181 --> 00:12:48,775
<i>He's my only friend!</i>

162
00:12:49,751 --> 00:12:51,548
- <i>But...</i>
- Look. He can't even dog paddle

163
00:12:51,619 --> 00:12:53,849
- even though he's a dog!
- <i>But...</i>

164
00:12:54,255 --> 00:12:58,055
<i>I'm sorry, Potchi...</i>
<i>I can't swim...</i>

165
00:12:59,093 --> 00:13:02,187
Hey! If you're his owner,
dive in after him!

166
00:13:09,370 --> 00:13:13,238
This is bad, Akane.
What if he can't swim?

167
00:13:15,476 --> 00:13:16,408
S-Save me!

168
00:13:17,011 --> 00:13:17,670
Leave him be.

169
00:13:18,613 --> 00:13:19,272
B-But...

170
00:13:20,982 --> 00:13:24,042
Then why don't <i>you</i> go
save him if you like?

171
00:13:26,454 --> 00:13:29,184
<i>I-I don't want to die...</i>
<i>Somebody save me!</i>

172
00:13:32,393 --> 00:13:33,291
P-Potchi!

173
00:13:34,862 --> 00:13:35,886
Potchi!

174
00:13:36,464 --> 00:13:37,988
I'm gonna digress, but...

175
00:13:38,800 --> 00:13:41,598
Potchi learned
how to dog paddle then.

176
00:13:45,073 --> 00:13:46,438
Potchi!

177
00:13:53,681 --> 00:13:55,649
Shooting Star escaped. Get him!

178
00:14:07,295 --> 00:14:11,288
<i>Ohhh... I can't breathe...</i>
<i>This... is it...</i>

179
00:14:18,539 --> 00:14:20,131
Are you awake, boy?

180
00:14:25,613 --> 00:14:28,707
I gave those kids
a good scolding.

181
00:14:29,450 --> 00:14:30,576
Here, eat!

182
00:14:32,153 --> 00:14:34,280
<i>Is this God? Oh...</i>

183
00:14:34,822 --> 00:14:36,915
Did you... save me?

184
00:14:37,759 --> 00:14:40,785
Just eat! Start with that.

185
00:14:42,964 --> 00:14:45,558
I see. You were betrayed
by your dog, too...

186
00:14:46,334 --> 00:14:50,202
In my country, dogs are creatures
that have a keen sense of loyalty...

187
00:14:50,838 --> 00:14:53,773
Well, you betrayed
your dog's trust first,

188
00:14:53,841 --> 00:14:55,308
so there's nothing
you can do about that.

189
00:14:57,045 --> 00:14:59,707
I was scared and couldn't move.

190
00:15:02,417 --> 00:15:04,078
I wanted to save him...

191
00:15:04,552 --> 00:15:07,214
But... I have no guts, so...

192
00:15:07,555 --> 00:15:08,647
That's right.

193
00:15:09,924 --> 00:15:12,984
Of course a kid your age
would be scared.

194
00:15:14,696 --> 00:15:15,788
But you know... boy.

195
00:15:16,564 --> 00:15:18,225
Just remember this.

196
00:15:18,766 --> 00:15:19,198
Huh?

197
00:15:20,268 --> 00:15:23,066
If you're a man choose
a lifestyle you won't regret...

198
00:15:25,239 --> 00:15:27,935
For things I truly
hold dear to myself,

199
00:15:28,176 --> 00:15:31,407
I'll protect them until the very end
with both these arms.

200
00:15:31,646 --> 00:15:34,672
Even if it's tough, or sad,
I'll stick it out...

201
00:15:34,749 --> 00:15:37,377
even if it looks like
I might lose my life!

202
00:15:41,889 --> 00:15:43,447
His name was Kaiza and

203
00:15:43,825 --> 00:15:48,228
he was a fisherman who'd come to this land
from another country in search of his dreams.

204
00:15:49,163 --> 00:15:52,291
After that, Inari really took to Kaiza.

205
00:15:52,734 --> 00:15:55,862
It may have been because Inari
had lost his real father

206
00:15:55,937 --> 00:15:57,871
when he was too young
to remember anything.

207
00:15:58,206 --> 00:16:01,232
But he was very attached to Kaiza.

208
00:16:01,309 --> 00:16:02,708
They were like father and son...

209
00:16:04,612 --> 00:16:07,376
It didn't take long
for Kaiza to become...

210
00:16:07,849 --> 00:16:09,817
a member of the family.

211
00:16:11,919 --> 00:16:15,787
And he was a man
this town needed.

212
00:16:16,691 --> 00:16:18,556
We... we've got trouble, Kaiza!

213
00:16:18,760 --> 00:16:20,955
The river dam has broken
from this rain!

214
00:16:21,262 --> 00:16:23,628
At this rate,
District D will be consumed!

215
00:16:23,965 --> 00:16:24,624
What?!

216
00:16:24,932 --> 00:16:25,489
Dad!

217
00:16:25,800 --> 00:16:27,700
Inari, go out back and
get some rope!

218
00:16:27,835 --> 00:16:28,267
Okay!

219
00:16:29,237 --> 00:16:29,828
Its no good!

220
00:16:30,104 --> 00:16:31,935
The only thing we can do is
to attach a rope and pull...

221
00:16:32,407 --> 00:16:34,967
Don't talk nonsense!
How are we going to attach a rope?!

222
00:16:35,276 --> 00:16:38,074
We'd die if we were to go
into such a furious current!

223
00:16:38,346 --> 00:16:41,110
But if we drag our feet,
District D will be annihilated!

224
00:16:41,516 --> 00:16:42,540
What should we do?

225
00:16:43,084 --> 00:16:43,743
I'll do it.

226
00:16:46,521 --> 00:16:47,180
Kaiza!

227
00:16:47,688 --> 00:16:48,848
Don't be foolish!

228
00:16:49,157 --> 00:16:50,852
Even you wouldn't be able to!

229
00:16:51,659 --> 00:16:52,318
Dad!

230
00:16:52,960 --> 00:16:54,154
Don't worry...

231
00:16:54,996 --> 00:16:56,361
Your dad's unmatched.

232
00:16:56,964 --> 00:17:00,695
Your dad loves the town
you're from, so...

233
00:17:04,839 --> 00:17:07,535
<i>For things I truly hold dear to myself...</i>

234
00:17:16,217 --> 00:17:18,310
<i>Even if I lose my life...</i>

235
00:17:21,556 --> 00:17:24,457
<i>I'll protect them to the end...</i>
<i>with both these arms!</i>

236
00:17:26,627 --> 00:17:28,959
Dad, hang in there!

237
00:17:36,571 --> 00:17:39,563
He did it!
The rope... the rope's attached!

238
00:17:39,640 --> 00:17:41,540
Okay, everybody pull!

239
00:17:41,609 --> 00:17:42,633
Yeah!

240
00:17:43,578 --> 00:17:47,844
From then on... the people of this land
called Kaiza a hero.

241
00:17:47,915 --> 00:17:52,215
And he became a father
that Inari could be proud of.

242
00:17:53,754 --> 00:17:57,281
It was around that time when Gato
set his sights on this land.

243
00:17:57,625 --> 00:18:00,219
And then, one night...

244
00:18:14,408 --> 00:18:15,602
I heard...

245
00:18:15,877 --> 00:18:18,812
That you're going to protect
this town with those arms...

246
00:18:26,387 --> 00:18:28,446
I dare you to!

247
00:18:59,253 --> 00:19:00,220
Listen up!

248
00:19:00,588 --> 00:19:04,957
This man resisted through force,
the policies of the Gato corporation

249
00:19:05,026 --> 00:19:07,153
and disturbed the order
of this nation.

250
00:19:08,262 --> 00:19:10,423
Therefore, he will now be executed!

251
00:19:17,038 --> 00:19:21,304
I just hope that such trivial matters
will never occur again.

252
00:19:21,709 --> 00:19:22,334
Dad!

253
00:19:23,077 --> 00:19:24,271
Stop, Inari...

254
00:19:32,453 --> 00:19:33,147
Do it...

255
00:19:37,491 --> 00:19:38,185
Dad...

256
00:19:44,532 --> 00:19:46,022
Dad!

257
00:19:54,408 --> 00:19:55,898
Didn't you tell me?

258
00:19:59,880 --> 00:20:02,906
That you'd... protect...

259
00:20:07,455 --> 00:20:11,516
me and the people of this land...
with both your arms?

260
00:20:12,893 --> 00:20:15,123
Dad, you liar...

261
00:20:19,300 --> 00:20:22,531
Ever since then,
Inari has changed...

262
00:20:23,337 --> 00:20:25,805
as well as Tsunami...
and the townspeople...

263
00:20:30,011 --> 00:20:34,380
Hero, that's just stupid.
There's no such thing!

264
00:20:52,366 --> 00:20:54,129
What're you doing, Naruto?

265
00:20:54,535 --> 00:20:57,993
You've had enough training for today.
You've built up too much Chakra.

266
00:20:58,539 --> 00:21:00,063
You'll die if you move
any more than that.

267
00:21:01,475 --> 00:21:02,772
I'll prove it.

268
00:21:04,578 --> 00:21:05,442
Prove what?

269
00:21:08,182 --> 00:21:09,171
I'll prove that...

270
00:21:09,784 --> 00:21:12,548
there <i>are</i> heroes...

271
00:21:16,157 --> 00:21:17,317
in this world!

272
00:22:52,572 --> 00:22:54,699
Huh? What do you want, lady?

273
00:22:55,041 --> 00:22:56,531
As for me, I'm training right now.

274
00:22:56,609 --> 00:22:58,702
Cuz we don't know when
Zabuza will strike next...

275
00:22:59,445 --> 00:23:02,573
Getting strong for someone special
is something I understand very well.

276
00:23:02,815 --> 00:23:05,375
So I'm going to get
stronger and stronger.

277
00:23:06,018 --> 00:23:09,112
I'll show Inari that there are heroes
in this world.

278
00:23:10,490 --> 00:23:13,755
Next time:
"Battle on the Bridge! Zabuza Returns!"

279
00:23:13,826 --> 00:23:16,420
As for me, I'm going to
kick butt once again!
